HEADWORD: Chamaecytisus
<hw>Chamaecytisus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of small
late-flowering trees or subshrubs having yellow to red flowers and
leathery or woody pods; -- often used especially for those formerly
included in genus <gen>Cytisus</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Chamaecytisus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

